I looked at ScheduledAnnotationBeanPostProcessor and any Set that is a value of the scheduledTasks map will only contain one task associated to the last `@Scheduled` annotated method of a bean because when there is a previous Set already created, it is always overwritten on [line 400](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/v4.3.0.RC2/spring-context/src/main/java/org/springframework/scheduling/annotation/ScheduledAnnotationBeanPostProcessor.java#L400).

