During singleton creation, `DefaultSingletonBeanRegistry` synchronises on `this.singletonObjects`:

https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/b1171d82967cfd374f0b08f9580fe662fa1a98e8/spring-beans/src/main/java/org/springframework/beans/factory/support/DefaultSingletonBeanRegistry.java#L204

While synchronized, it then uses the `singletonFactory` to create the singleton:

https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-framework/blob/b1171d82967cfd374f0b08f9580fe662fa1a98e8/spring-beans/src/main/java/org/springframework/beans/factory/support/DefaultSingletonBeanRegistry.java#L222

This call into user code while holding a lock can result in deadlock. We've seen one example reported in [this Spring Boot issue](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/17765) where Micrometer is also involved. I've also reproduced a very similar problem without Micrometer and with no synchronization in user code:

