But, webflux's result is defferent. 
```
@GetMapping(""vehicle"")
public Mono<Vehicle> getVehicle() {
    return Mono.just(new Car());
}
```
It only supports a 'content-type: text/event-stream' when return type is a mono of interface.
Is it a bug?']",['closed'],[3],"['This odd. The signature with `Mono<Vehicle>` should work in both Spring MVC and WebFlux as expected. Do you have a sample?', 'Here is my simple example.

